      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Robocall Enforcement Enhancement Act of 2018</strong></p> <p>This bill amends the Communications Act of 1934: </p> <ul> <li>to lengthen the statute of limitations from two years to three&nbsp;years&nbsp;for pursuing caller identification information violations (known as "spoofing"), </li> <li>to &nbsp;lengthen the statute of limitations from one year to three years for pursing automated telephone equipment violations (known as "robocalls"), and </li> <li>to authorize the Federal Communications Commission (FCC)&nbsp;to impose forfeiture penalties without first sending a citation regarding the charged violation against persons not licensed by the FCC who violate prohibitions on the use of automated telephone equipment.</li></ul>]]></text>
